pokemon.Description: Elite guardians of the ancient empire, Praetorvus were feared for their combination of military might and political influence. Their purple-trimmed armor marked them as extensions of imperial authority.

primary.name: Praetorian Guard
primary.description: This Pokémon may take hits for allies that are within its range of movement. If an ally in range is targeted by an attack, this Pokémon may spend unspent movement to move next to its ally out of turn without provoking attacks of opportunity. The attack against the ally will be rolled against this Pokémon's AC instead of the intended target.

secondary.name: Light Armor
secondary.description: This Pokémon takes 25% reduced damage from super effective moves, rounded down.

hidden.name: Imperial Authority
hidden.description:
This Pokémon has advantage on intimidation and persuation checks, and may use an action to automatically frighten enemies that can see it for 1d4 rounds.
Additionally, three times per long rest, this Pokémon may use its bonus action to override the ability of another Pokémon it can see.
